
[1]olate

   OLATE, v.t. [L. To lay waste, alone.]

   1. To deprive of inhabitants; to make desert. The earth was nearly
   desolated by the flood.

   2. To lay waste; to ruin; to ravage; to destroy improvements or works
   of art. An inundation desolates fields. Whole countries have been
   desolated by armies.
